node.text:
At first glance, @jesshart's modeling career reads like a fairy-tale success story. But it took the Australian-born model years to realize her true passion. To us, she is unapologetic about admitting that her heart beats more for smoking wheels than for the smoke and mirrors of the fashion world. In our new episode of AMG Uncovered, Jess explains how important it was to overcome the common stereotypes in order to unlock her true self.

Music: 86Tales

node.text: The inaugural version of the 1952 W194 300 SL Coupe was built for the track. Highlighted by victories at the 24 Hours of Le Mans and Carrera Panamericana in Mexico, it was powered by a 3.0-liter, SOHC straight-6 engine and was then placed on a welded tubular frame chassis that weighed less than 150 pounds. Creating a highly rigid chassis could not be achieved with traditional door openings, paving the way for the iconic “Gullwing” doors. Thus began the iconic mix of technological innovation and breathtaking aesthetics that define the SL line to this day. #W194 #Coupe #PebbleBeachConcours #MercedesBenz
